        <h2 id="what-is">What is SE Ranking?</h2>
        <p>SE Ranking is an all-in-one SEO platform built for agencies and small teams who need reliable rank tracking, solid site audits, and actionable keyword data at a price that does not eat their margin.</p>

        <p>The platform started as a rank tracker and expanded into a full SEO suite covering keyword research, site auditing, backlink analysis, competitor research, content editing, and AI search visibility tracking. The core thesis: most SEO teams do not need every feature Semrush offers — they need the essentials done well, at a price they can pass through to clients without losing margin.</p>

        <p>What SE Ranking is <em>not</em>: a content creation service, an automated publishing platform, or a done-for-you SEO system. It tells you where you rank, what is broken on your site, and what keywords your competitors target. You still write every article, optimise every page, and publish every piece of content manually.</p>

        <div class="callout callout-info">
          <div class="callout-label">Company background</div>
          <p>2013, founded by Valery Kurilov. Headquartered in <strong>London with offices in Palo Alto, Kyiv, Wrocław, and Warsaw</strong>. Bootstrapped — no venture capital, no outside funding. Hundreds of thousands of users worldwide. The company has grown consistently without outside investment, which keeps the product team accountable to users rather than investors.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="features">SE Ranking features — the full 2026 walkthrough</h2>
        <p>The feature surface is broad. Here is what actually matters in daily use, broken down by module.</p>

        <h3>1. Rank Tracking</h3>
        <p>Daily desktop, mobile, and local rank tracking across 230+ regional Google databases. Accuracy benchmarked at 94.3% vs AccuRanker in our side-by-side test. Includes SERP feature tracking, competitor ranking comparison, and Share of Voice.</p>

        <h3>2. Keyword Research</h3>
        <p>Database covers 7+ billion keywords across the same 230+ regions. Volume, difficulty, CPC, and SERP analysis. Smaller than Semrush's 26B but covers all major commercial markets. Keyword grouping and intent classification included.</p>

        <h3>3. Site Audit</h3>
        <p>120+ technical SEO checks. Crawl depth, internal linking, hreflang, schema, Core Web Vitals. Crawler is slightly slower than Ahrefs at scale but catches the same issues.</p>

        <h3>4. Backlink Checker</h3>
        <p>Backlink index is smaller than Ahrefs (data sourced via partnerships) but adequate for most agency use cases. Toxic backlink detection and disavow file export included.</p>

        <h3>5. Competitor Research</h3>
        <p>Domain Overview tool reveals competitor keywords, traffic estimates, top pages, and backlink profiles. Useful for client onboarding presentations.</p>

        <h3>6. White-Label Reports</h3>
        <p>Branded PDF reports, custom domains, and client portals on the Pro plan and above. <strong>Genuinely the best white-label experience in this price tier</strong> — used as the primary differentiator by small agencies.</p>

        <h3>7. AI Visibility Tracker</h3>
        <p>Newer module that tracks visibility in AI search engines (ChatGPT search, Perplexity, Google AI Overviews). Still early but a meaningful addition for 2026 buyers.</p>

        <h2 id="pricing">SE Ranking pricing — what it really costs in 2026</h2>
